events.name: GDG Valley DevFest 2016
events.description:
NOTE: BUY TICKETS HERE: https://valleydevfest.com/

The biggest Google tech conference in the California Central Valley carefully crafted for you by GDG community! All about Android, Web and Cloud from the world experts. 

Google Developer Groups Fresno, Modesto, Oakdale, and Visalia have combined powers to offer a one day, 20+ talks, four parallel track extravaganza! Some of our speakers include:

• Paul Bakus, Web Developer Advocate at Google 

• Sandeep Dinesh, Cloud Developer Advocate at Google 

• Martin Omander, GDG Regional Lead North America at Google 

• Nilay Yener, Community Advocate at Google

• Murat Yener, Android Software Developer at Intel

• Justin Ribeiro, Google Developer Expert in Web, IoT, and Wearables 

• and so many more! https://valleydevfest.com/speakers 

We expect another +350 event this year and tickets are going fast! To attend the event, buy a ticket from https://www.eventbrite.com/e/valleydevfestcom-tickets-27337601502 or visit https://valleydevfest.com/ for more details.

We hope to see you there!

events.name: Resources and advice for tech contractors from our friends at The Shire!
events.description: Hi GDG Modesto and friends of The Shire Community! Join us on Wednesday, July 18 at 6p at Valley Worx (4701 Stoddard St., Modesto) for a very practical discussion presented by The Shire Community Tech Committee: Protecting your Interests and Reputation while working as an Independent Contractor. Justin Brown and Jonathan Bryant will present their experiences working with small local businesses and medium to large organizations. They answer how freelance developers and small start up teams can deal with signed agreements, non-disclosure agreements, government agencies, open-source bias, and communication issues in such a way as to protect your hard work. Followed by a Shire Blurb and an open Q&A.

events.name: Google Cloud Study Jam: Intro to Machine Learning

venue.name: MJC East - College Ave & Stoddard Ave

events.description:
Join us for our Cloud Study Jam on Wednesday Feb 13 at MJC East Campus CAT building Jeremy Lab (room 231 or near there :) )

Get official Google training, a $55+ value, free of charge. Together we'll work through several Google Cloud labs. You will get hands-on experience with Machine Learning in Google's Cloud Platform.

Then after our live session, you will have free access to more labs you can finish at home like Security, IoT, Kubernetes, and Google Cloud certification prep. Complete all labs in the quest and earn a Google-hosted badge for your online profile, and additional 30 days access to the training platform to compete any labs you want.

Bring a laptop and charger (PC, Mac or Chromebook)! The labs will run on all of the latest versions of the popular browsers. For the best experience, make sure your laptop has Firefox or Chrome installed. Don’t forget your charger.

Hi GDGers, Since we didn't quite get to the Machine Learning portion of the Cloud Study Jams in February, please join us for our TensorFlow Summit Viewing Party on Wednesday March 13th at 6pm at MJC East Campus CAT building Jeremy Lab (room 231 or near there :) )

TensorFlow is an open source software library for high performance numerical computation. Its flexible architecture allows easy deployment of computation across a variety of platforms (CPUs, GPUs, TPUs), and from desktops to clusters of servers to mobile and edge devices.

Originally developed by researchers and engineers from the Google Brain team within Google’s AI organization, it comes with strong support for machine learning and deep learning and the flexible numerical computation core is used across many other scientific domains.

We hope to see you there! Also, our friends at Women Techmakers Fresno will be hosting a full day International Women's Day event on March 9, more info and tickets here: https://www.eventbrite.com/e/mind-the-gap-international-womens-day-celebration-2019-tickets-55545077823
events.how_to_find_us: CAT building 2nd floor, Jeremy Lab room 231-ish (look for meetup signs)

events.name: Next '19 Extended Modesto
events.description: Join us on Wednesday, April 17 at 6pm at the MJC East Campus CAT building room 231 (Jeremy Lab) for this year's Cloud Next Extended event. We will be sharing clips, demos and labs from the Cloud Next Conference. We'll also be brainstorming plans for our summer meetups some come ready with your ideas! Hope to see you there!
events.how_to_find_us: CAT building Jeremy Lab (room 231)

events.name: I/O Extended Modesto
events.description: Join us at the Jeremy Lab in the MJC East Campus CAT building (room 231) for I/O Extended Modesto on Wednesday, May 15, 2019 at 6pm. We'll be reviewing the big announcements, watching highlight clips, as well as introducing some of the code labs from I/O. And yes, there will be pizza ;)
events.how_to_find_us: Jeremy Lab in the CAT building (room 231)

events.name: Women Techmakers Modesto 1st Event
events.description: 2nd Floor of the AMR Building!!! Join us for an inspiring event introducing Women Techmakers to Modesto. Google's Women Techmakers program provides visibility, community, and resources for women in technology. We are excited to see this community grow and hope to meet you all. Swag and prizes will be distributed until supplies last.

events.name: WTM Night
events.description: Please join us for another event as the Women Techmakers community continues to grow. We will have a guest speaker and will be starting a code lab, remember beginners are welcome. Please bring your laptops

upcoming.name: Women Techmakers Night
upcoming.description: We will be joined by the super cool gamer, Luz Gutierrez. She is the owner of The Gaming Hub in Modesto and is currently completing her computer science degree. Don't miss Luz at our next Women Techmakers event.

upcoming.name: Save the Date! Modesto-Berkeley DevFest 2019
upcoming.description: Hey GDGers, we know October is a long ways out, but we're super excited to bring you the first DevFest to be hosted in Modesto (and our second partnering with GDG Berkeley)! Location is TBD, but the date will be October 19, 2019 so mark your calendars now and get ready for a day full of awesome technology content and great people.

answers.question: What is the most important problem facing our local community?
answers.answer: I think the lack of career opportunities for young people is one of the most important challenges we face.

answers.question: How can we use technology to solve this problem?
answers.answer: By fostering an interest and developing expertise in technology, I think we can create more careers in the area.

answers.question: What is your favorite Google technology or Open Source project?

group_profile.intro: I've lived in modesto my whole life and have been working as a developer in san francisco for the last 15 years.  I want to meet other developers in the area and hope we can put our heads together to solve problems in our local community!
